-- Deutsche Bank CEO says German banks have likely passed ECB test
-- By Matthias Sobolewski
-- Thu Oct 23, 2014 10:42AM EDT
-- None



BERLIN, Oct 23 (Reuters) - Deutsche bank <DBKGn.DE> co-Chief Executive Juergen Fitschen on Thursday said German lenders will likely have passed a stress test being organised by the European Central Bank.

"When you listen to the news on Sunday, you will likely hear that all German banks have passed the stress tests," Fitschen, who is also president of BdB association of German private-sector banks, said at an event in Berlin.